    &lt;CommentText&gt;Having turned up with my son experiencing chest pain and shortness of breath an initial wait time of 3 and half hours seemed poor but still waiting to be seen by a doctor 9 hours later was disgusting. Numerous requests to staff were met with its always like this 9 hours not bad, 12 hours would be bad. On top of this the parking fees needed to cover such an atrocious wait were tantamount to theft. 

I could have driven to London and caught a flight to another country and still been seen more quickly. If this is the future of the NHS then give up now pretending itâ€™s free at point if need.

Visits in the past always took time but in this day and age the public deserve much better than the service delivered and the half hearted apologies that accompany it.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
